    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD3S is a superlative example of rotary engineering, retained in its original factory configuration. The heart of this specimen is the 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged engine, delivering a seamless power band with consistent compression pulses across all rotor faces. The chassis remains taut, featuring the original four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential for precision handling. All critical maintenance has been addressed, including a high-temperature silicone vacuum line refresh and a comprehensive cooling system update to mitigate thermal stress. With no modifications to the ECU or exhaust architecture, this vehicle offers the pure, unadulterated driving dynamics intended by Hiroshima\u2019s engineers. A collector-grade find with zero structural oxidation or interior UV degradation.",
